The paper deals with vehicular mobility and proposes a method for large-scale monitoring and analysis of spatio-temporal models using webcams. This involves network infrastructure and computer vision techniques, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NI (Networks and Internet Architecture) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the algorithm used for processing and analyzing the data, which involves statistical methods and cryptography, relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with the generation and analysis of a large dataset, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
